OL,4,CCzech women win MPs' backing for
OL,5,Cnon-gendered surnames
OL,6, Women in the Czech Republic may soon be
OL,7, able to take non-gendered versions of
OL,8, their surnames after MPs backed a
OL,9, change in the law.
OL,11,FIn the Czech language, the ending
OL,12,F"-ova" is added to all surnames for
OL,13,Fwomen, so Mr Novak's daughter becomes
OL,14,FMs Novakova.
OL,16,FWomen have only been able to drop the
OL,17,F"-ova" ending in limited circumstances,
OL,18,Fsuch as if they have foreign
OL,19,Fnationality or live with a foreigner.
OL,21,FThe senate will now vote on the change.
